HEADWORD: Diazeutic
<hw>Di`a*zeu"tic</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ disjunctive, fr. <?/
to disjoin; <grk>dia`</grk> through, asunder + <?/ to join, yoke.]</ety>
<fld>(Anc. Mus.)</fld> <def>Disjoining two fourths; <as>as, the
<ex>diazeutic</ex> tone, which, like that from F to G in modern music,
lay between two fourths, and, being joined to either, made a
fifth</as>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
